Designed to overcome the connectivity, security, and control challenges associated with capturing real-time session recordings in IP telephony and unified communications (UC) environments, the solution is highly extensible with a rich feature set. Service providers and enterprises deploy it in compliance and quality assurance applications, and enterprise IT organizations use it to deliver private cloud-based session recording services.

Title 1: Oracle Communications Evolved Communications Application Server Documentation
Meta Description 1: Oracle Communications Evolved Communications Application Server enables you to provide SIP multimedia services to your IMS subscribers. It contains a Voice over Long Term Evolution (VoLTE) and Wi-Fi-based VOIP (VoWiFi) application that you can modify and expand to define the services that you offer to your subscribers. It includes an easy-to-use GUI interface for modifying SIP call behavior and session control logic and provides drag-and-drop control over the workflow from creation through to testing, staging, and ultimately production.

Title 1: Oracle Communications Convergent Charging Controller Documentation
Meta Description 1: Oracle Communications Convergent Charging Controller applications enable communications service providers to control telephony sessions and events, to integrate network elements with online charging systems, and to provide voucher based recharge services. Use Convergent Charging Controller to manage telephony and messaging services, define rules for telephony session and event control, provide device based self-care, and to integrate with charging systems for online authorization of sessions and events.

Meta Description 1: Oracle Communications EAGLE is a signaling platform that extends signal transfer point (STP) and signaling gateway (SGW) assets to LTE, M2M and Wi-Fi domains for enhanced connectivity, capacity and revenue.  As part of an intelligent evolution towards LTE, EAGLE converges key SS7 assets onto a single signaling platform. EAGLE delivers SS7-focused STP and SGW assets that help operators better manage intelligent routing, screening services, number portability (NP), equipment identify register and integrated performance/service management from the same database technology and footprint.  As they build out the LTE portions of their network, operators gain seamless connections to PSTN SS7/TDM transports.

Title 1: Oracle Communications Network Charging and Control Documentation
Meta Description 1: Oracle Communications Network Charging and Control (NCC) applications enable communications service providers to control telephony sessions and events, to integrate network elements with online charging systems, and to provide voucher based recharge services. Use NCC to manage telephony and messaging services, define rules for telephony session and event control, provide device based self-care, and to integrate with charging systems for online authorization of sessions and events.

Title 1: Oracle Communications Instant Messaging Server Documentation
Meta Description 1: Oracle Communications Instant Messaging Server provides a secure, real-time communication and collaboration system, combining presence awareness with instant messaging capabilities, for communications service providers. Use Instant Messaging Server to create XMPP-based services, use client-to-client voice chat, enable mobile presence services, and access SIP/SIMPLE networks.

Oracle Acme Packet platforms are purpose-built hardware designs that tightly integrate with Acme Packet OS, to provide the critical controls for delivering trusted, first-class real-time communications--voice, video, and multimedia sessions--across Internet Protocol (IP) network borders.

Oracle Communications Policy Management is a sophisticated policy and charging rules function (PCRF) designed to shape detailed policies that determine how and under what conditions subscribers and applications use network resources. It is designed so that operators can easily add and re-configure the triggers, conditions and actions governed by policies, such as subscriber tiers and entitlements, bandwidth and data volumes, etc.

Title 1: Oracle Communications Subscriber-Aware Load Balancer Documentation
Meta Description 1: Oracle Communications Subscriber-Aware Load Balancer enables linear, non-disruptive scaling of capacity to two million subscribers from a single Session Initiation Protocol (SIP) Internet Protocol (IP) address. It supports the delivery of any IP Multimedia Subsystem (IMS), Rich Communications Services (RCS), or next-generation network (NGN) service as well as any SIP application -- voice, video, presence, messaging, and multimedia -- over any mobile or fixed line access network, including the internet.

Title 1: Oracle Communications Diameter Signaling Router Documentation
Meta Description 1: Oracle Communications Diameter Signaling Router is a market-leading cloud-ready Diameter signaling  controller solution that centralizes routing, traffic management and load balancing, creating an architecture that enables IMS and LTE networks to be truly elastic and adapt to increasing service and traffic demands while optimizing the network resources.

Title 1: Oracle Communications WebRTC Session Controller Documentation

For example, developers can incorporate functions such as video chats, audio communications, and data transfers into their Web applications.

Oracle Communications Contacts Server is an Internet standards-based address book server. Use Contacts Server to store and organize contact information, create and share address books, and integrate contact information with corporate directories.

Title 1: Oracle Communications Converged Application Server, Service Controller Documentation

It enables CSPs to launch innovative new services that blend legacy and Internet Protocol (IP) networks.

Online Mediation Controller can manage communication between network applications and charging systems to handle authentication, authorization, and accounting (AAA).

Oracle Communications Session Router is a next generation session routing proxy that incorporates both IETF SIP proxy & 3GPP Breakout Gateway Control Functions (BGCF) is specifically design to control the routing of large volumes of SIP session signaling messages. Session Router provides high-performance SIP routing with scalable routing policies that increase overall network capacity and reduce costs. It plays a central role in Oracle's open session routing (OSR) architecture and helps service providers build a scalable, next-generation signaling core for SIP-based services.
